result.name: Sun Heung Yuen (Kin Kee)

reviews.text: Good beef omelet sandwich. The French toast is on the thinner side. It's nice and crispy though. The milk tea was too watered down and doesn't have a strong tea taste.
Super tasty beef omelette sandwich. Make sure to add the extra $1 to have the bread toasted. Of course, don't expect quality beef as it's just simple local food.

Sham Shui Po is a really local district, in other words, there are many local restaurants that sell gourmet at really reasonable price. Sun Hang Yuen (Kin Kee) is one of them, and I came here for their sandwich.

For HKD$22, I got this delicious Toasted Beef Omelette Sandwich (HKD$1 went for toasting). The bread was crispy and good. And the sandwich was actually better than I thought it would be! I was expecting minced beef and scramble egg, but it was actually beef pieces wrapped in omelette. Extraordinarily good! Especially when the omelette was still a tiny bit runny! Nom!

Does not live up to its hype. Was interested to check it out after seeing some YouTube recommendations. However I left sorely disappointed for an out of the way trip here. Beef sandwich is just toast with beef omelette in it. Not something extraordinary. Palatable but not outstanding with super tender and juicy beef omelette kind of stuff. Noodles are the worst bunch in the menu. Soup comes with noodles ammonia smell to it. Although the noodles are crunchy and pork trotter version is tender, by HK standards any decent noodles shop could made the cut or had done better.

Famous for their beef omelette sandwich n tried both plain and toasted bread beef omelette sandwich. Also ordered their Tong Fun beef noodles. Nothing really special. Including 2 drinks cost abt HK$100.
